

=Bio=

"Andrew “bunnie” Huang is a nocturnal hacker and the hardware lead at chumby Industries; his responsibilities include the architecture, design and production of chumby devices, as well as the strategic planning and ecosystem development of the broader chumby hardware platform. With a PhD in EE from MIT, he has completed several major projects, ranging from hacking the Xbox, to designing the world’s first fully-integrated photonic-silicon chips running at 10 Gbps with Luxtera, Inc."

